  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 1.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - In the Hebrew text this verse stands as the last of ch. 1. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Determined",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Hebrew word is the ordinary word for \"said;\" as, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "e.g.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the expression of such frequent occurrence, \"The Lord said.\" Its natural equivalent here might be, he ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "gave the word",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "issued the command",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for the building of a house. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For the Name of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; better, to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the Name of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 5:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; or in Hebrew text, 5:18; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The expression,\" the Name of the Lord,\" is of very early date (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 4:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). A name named upon a person at the first purported as far as possible to mark his ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "nature",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", either its ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "tout ensemble",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or some striking attribute of it. Hence the changed name, sometimes of Divine interposition (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 17:5, 15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 32:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 35:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); and much more noticeably the alterations of the Divine Name, to serve and to mark the progressive development of the revelation of God to man (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 17:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 3:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
